        <h4>About</h4>
        <p>
          HistoriKC's mission is to make Kansas City's history more accessible. Historic photos often allow us to relate to the
          city of the past, but navigating long lists of photos can sometimes make it difficult to connect present-day locations
          with the history. I hope this map is able to make these historic photos more relatable, accessible, and enjoyable!
        </p>
        <p>
          Please follow <a href="http://twitter.com/historikc">@historikc on Twitter</a> for updates, and feel free to direct any
          questions or feedback there! If you would like photos from the same sources as HistoriKC delivered to you on social media,
          follow <a href="http://twitter.com/historicpicskc">@historicpicskc on Twitter</a>.
        </p>
        <h4>Photos</h4>
        <p>
          All photos on this site are sourced from the Missouri Valley Special Collections, Kansas City Public Library, Kansas City, Missouri.
        </p>
        <h4>Site</h4>
        <p>
          This site was created by <a href="http://twitter.com/kyledrowan">Kyle Rowan</a>, a software guy with a passion for Kansas City
          and its amazing history. Inspiration came from the <a href="http://oldnyc.org">OldNYC</a> site.
          The site is open-sourced on the <a href="http://github.com/kyledrowan/historikc-rails">historikc-rails</a> GitHub repository, and I
          welcome any contributions!
        </p>
